WEBVTT

1
00:00:51.885 --> 00:00:53.716
I am actress Milla Jovovich...

2
00:00:53.787 --> 00:00:57.086
...and I will be portraying
Dr. Abigail Tyler in The Fourth Kind.

3
00:00:57.157 --> 00:00:58.522
This film is a dramatization.

4
00:00:58.591 --> 00:01:01.992
...of events that occurred October
1st through the 9th of 2000...

5
00:01:02.062 --> 00:01:03.620
...in the northern
Alaskan town of Nome.

6
00:01:03.696 --> 00:01:05.721
To better explain
the events of the story...

7
00:01:05.799 --> 00:01:07.357
...the director has
included actual.

8
00:01:07.434 --> 00:01:08.924
...archived footage
throughout the film.

9
00:01:09.002 --> 00:01:12.403
This footage was acquired from
Nome psychologist Dr. Abigail Tyler...

10
00:01:12.472 --> 00:01:17.068
who has personally documented over
65 hours of video and audio materials.

11
00:01:17.143 --> 00:01:18.269
...during the time
of the incidents.

12
00:01:18.344 --> 00:01:20.209
To better
protect their privacy...

13
00:01:20.280 --> 00:01:22.111
we have changed
the names and professions.

14
00:01:22.182 --> 00:01:23.479
...of many of
the people involved.

15
00:01:23.550 --> 00:01:26.018
Every dramatized scene
in this movie is supported.

16
00:01:26.086 --> 00:01:28.145
...by either
archived audio. video...

17
00:01:28.221 --> 00:01:30.212
...or as it was related
by Dr. Tyler.

18
00:01:30.290 --> 00:01:32.281
...during extensive interviews
with the director.

19
00:01:32.358 --> 00:01:35.020
In the end. what you
believe is yours to decide.

20
00:01:35.095 --> 00:01:37.393
Please be advised
that some of what.

21
00:01:37.464 --> 00:01:40.331
...you are about to see
is extremely disturbing.

22
00:01:41.501 --> 00:01:45.232
Just relax.
and I'll ask you questions...

23
00:01:45.305 --> 00:01:46.863
...and whenever. whatever
you want to toss in there.

24
00:01:46.940 --> 00:01:48.430
- Okay.
- You all right?

25
00:01:48.508 --> 00:01:49.600
Okay.

26
00:01:49.709 --> 00:01:51.267
I'm going to try.

27
00:01:51.344 --> 00:01:56.077
...and make this as painless as possible.

28
00:01:57.050 --> 00:01:59.382
Can you state your
name for the camera?

29
00:01:59.519 --> 00:02:02.010
Dr. Abigail Emily Tyler.

30
00:02:03.423 --> 00:02:05.948
Okay. where would
you like to begin?

31
00:02:07.026 --> 00:02:08.357
I guess...

32
00:02:10.196 --> 00:02:14.724
After what happened with
Will. my husband. I...

33
00:02:15.935 --> 00:02:20.099
I went to my friend. who is
also a psychologist. Dr...

34
00:02:21.674 --> 00:02:25.872
...because I was having trouble
dealing with how he...

35
00:02:27.380 --> 00:02:29.905
With how it happened
and who did it.

36
00:02:31.017 --> 00:02:33.884
You don't think
you might need more time?

37
00:02:33.953 --> 00:02:39.585
No. this is something...
I have to do this.

38
00:02:41.294 --> 00:02:43.819
I have to remember
his face.

39
00:02:43.897 --> 00:02:46.764
I need it
for myself to heal.

40
00:02:48.101 --> 00:02:51.867
I have to try. and I have to
know that. for my children...

41
00:02:51.938 --> 00:02:54.532
...that I did everything
that I could.

42
00:02:55.175 --> 00:02:57.370
- To remember.
- ... To remember.

43
00:02:57.877 --> 00:03:01.142
You know. since that night.
Ashley still can't see...

44
00:03:02.015 --> 00:03:06.111
...and I don't think that she's
gonna get her sight back.

45
00:03:06.186 --> 00:03:09.747
...if she doesn't accept
what happened.

46
00:03:12.325 --> 00:03:16.591
Well. I think you both have the same
problem. just different symptoms.

47
00:03:20.333 --> 00:03:22.494
Yeah. and I think
that it could help.

48
00:03:22.569 --> 00:03:25.333
...if I could just remember
the face of that man...

49
00:03:26.206 --> 00:03:31.269
...so we could somehow track him
down and set the record straight.

50
00:03:33.379 --> 00:03:35.244
...and find some closure.

51
00:03:37.150 --> 00:03:40.347
All right. All right.

52
00:03:41.421 --> 00:03:43.582
Do you want it
on video?

53
00:03:43.656 --> 00:03:44.884
Yeah.

54
00:03:44.958 --> 00:03:50.055
Counseling a fellow
psychologist is like...

55
00:03:50.129 --> 00:03:51.460
It's like talking to myself.

56
00:03:55.535 --> 00:03:57.799
You always say that.

57
00:03:57.870 --> 00:04:00.566
I do? Oh. my God.

58
00:04:03.543 --> 00:04:04.874
All right.

59
00:04:06.813 --> 00:04:11.409
I guess just try to relax
and get yourself comfortable.

60
00:04:13.086 --> 00:04:15.850
Listen to the sound of
my voice as I count back.

61
00:04:17.523 --> 00:04:18.581
Ten...

62
00:04:19.692 --> 00:04:20.784
Nine...

63
00:04:21.527 --> 00:04:25.588
Eight. seven. six...

64
00:04:26.132 --> 00:04:27.463
Your eyes are
getting heavier...

65
00:04:27.533 --> 00:04:29.330
...and heavier.

66
00:04:29.569 --> 00:04:32.197
Five. four.

67
00:04:33.206 --> 00:04:35.071
- They're almost closed.
- They're almost closed.

68
00:04:35.141 --> 00:04:37.974
Three. two.

69
00:04:38.044 --> 00:04:39.341
...and one.

70
00:04:39.412 --> 00:04:40.436
...one.

71
00:04:44.651 --> 00:04:45.709
Very good. Abbey.
Very good.

72
00:04:45.785 --> 00:04:46.774
Very good. Abbey.
Very good.

73
00:04:47.086 --> 00:04:48.713
Let's go back in time...

74
00:04:48.788 --> 00:04:50.346
Let's go back in time...

75
00:04:50.957 --> 00:04:52.584
...back into the past...

76
00:04:52.659 --> 00:04:54.217
...back
into the past...

77
00:04:54.994 --> 00:04:57.292
...to the night of
August 2nd of this year.

78
00:04:57.430 --> 00:04:59.728
...to the night of
August 2nd of this year.

79
00:05:00.400 --> 00:05:02.231
What was the weather like?

80
00:05:02.302 --> 00:05:05.533
Warm.
Warmer than usual...

81
00:05:07.240 --> 00:05:10.607
...even though it's
raining outside.

82
00:05:11.577 --> 00:05:12.942
Okay. good.

83
00:05:14.147 --> 00:05:18.311
Now. let's go back to
when you were with Will...

84
00:05:19.385 --> 00:05:22.286
...just before the intruder
entered your room.

85
00:05:24.324 --> 00:05:25.985
We're making love.

86
00:05:28.928 --> 00:05:32.796
It's nice. It's so... It's so nice.

87
00:05:45.111 --> 00:05:46.874
He's falling asleep.

88
00:05:47.814 --> 00:05:48.940
Mmm.

89
00:05:50.216 --> 00:05:53.117
Good. So what happens...
What happened next?

90
00:05:53.553 --> 00:05:56.283
I'm awake.
I'm wide awake...

91
00:05:57.190 --> 00:06:02.184
...and we're just
lying here.

92
00:06:06.699 --> 00:06:08.257
What woke you up?

93
00:06:30.423 --> 00:06:32.084
Oh. God!

94
00:06:32.158 --> 00:06:36.026
Someone stabbed him in
the chest! Oh. my God!

95
00:06:37.930 --> 00:06:40.296
Blood everywhere.
There's blood everywhere.

96
00:06:40.366 --> 00:06:42.664
Try to see his face.
Try to see his face.

97
00:06:42.735 --> 00:06:43.724
I can't see it.

98
00:06:43.803 --> 00:06:45.134
My husband!

99
00:06:45.204 --> 00:06:46.865
It just feels like I
can't move. I can't see it.

100
00:06:46.939 --> 00:06:48.930
It feels like we're
frozen. I can't see it.

101
00:06:49.008 --> 00:06:52.671
Abbey. Abbey. Abbey.
Abbey. Abbey. Abbey.

102
00:06:52.745 --> 00:06:54.440
It's all over me!
All over me.

103
00:06:54.514 --> 00:06:56.141
Focus on my voice.
Focus on my voice.

104
00:06:56.215 --> 00:06:58.376
You will be awakened and conscious.

105
00:06:58.451 --> 00:07:00.146
...in five. four. three. two. one.

106
00:07:05.458 --> 00:07:08.791
Abbey. Here. Let me.

107
00:07:09.362 --> 00:07:11.557
If I could just
see his face.

108
00:07:13.800 --> 00:07:17.634
He was killed. and I was right
there. Abel. I was right there.

109
00:07:18.604 --> 00:07:21.767
Yeah. you know. it's
as natural to feel guilt.

110
00:07:21.841 --> 00:07:25.436
...as it is unnatural to
feel it was your fault.

111
00:07:26.746 --> 00:07:28.236
You know that.

112
00:07:32.785 --> 00:07:34.446
- Yeah. okay.
- Okay.

113
00:07:45.498 --> 00:07:49.025
I think you might want to
consider taking some time off.

114
00:07:50.403 --> 00:07:51.893
Real time. you know?

115
00:07:52.538 --> 00:07:56.406
Because it just might help you
find clarity with what happened.

116
00:07:56.476 --> 00:07:59.912
I have to continue this
study. It meant a lot to Will...

117
00:08:02.181 --> 00:08:04.911
...and he would have
wanted me to continue.

118
00:08:06.052 --> 00:08:07.815
Now. why did I know
you were gonna say that?

119
00:08:07.887 --> 00:08:09.548
He would have wanted
me to try and finish it.

120
00:08:09.622 --> 00:08:11.852
...as soon as I could.

121
00:08:12.492 --> 00:08:15.256
It meant a lot to him.

122
00:08:35.181 --> 00:08:37.513
And how long
had it been at this point.

123
00:08:37.583 --> 00:08:40.677
...since Will had
passed away?

124
00:08:41.654 --> 00:08:43.019
Two months.

125
00:08:43.289 --> 00:08:44.688
And you guys were
already back to school...

126
00:08:44.757 --> 00:08:46.418
...and the kids were
already back to school?

127
00:08:46.492 --> 00:08:52.124
I had to try and get some
normality back into life.

128
00:08:53.032 --> 00:08:55.262
I didn't know
what else to do.

129
00:09:03.543 --> 00:09:05.568
Is Nome a place you
can drive into or...

130
00:09:05.645 --> 00:09:07.078
No. you have to
fly around.

131
00:09:07.146 --> 00:09:08.170
Okay.

132
00:09:08.247 --> 00:09:10.374
You can't get there by road.

133
00:10:07.306 --> 00:10:08.364
Any messages?

134
00:10:08.441 --> 00:10:10.102
No. but Scott's waiting in your office...

135
00:10:10.176 --> 00:10:11.768
...and you have
a 1:00 and a 2:00.

136
00:10:11.844 --> 00:10:13.175
Thank you.

137
00:10:13.279 --> 00:10:14.541
So. how was it coming in?

138
00:10:14.614 --> 00:10:16.479
It was a little bumpy.

139
00:10:16.983 --> 00:10:18.450
You'd think as beautiful as that sky is.

140
00:10:18.517 --> 00:10:19.916
...that it wouldn't
be so rough.

141
00:10:19.986 --> 00:10:21.248
The stuff that
really shakes us...

142
00:10:21.320 --> 00:10:23.254
We seldom
ever see coming.

143
00:10:23.322 --> 00:10:24.380
I know. I know.

144
00:10:24.457 --> 00:10:25.856
It's a good saying.

145
00:10:25.958 --> 00:10:27.482
Not every week.

146
00:10:28.527 --> 00:10:30.518
Hi. Scott.
Sorry I'm late.

147
00:10:30.596 --> 00:10:32.223
Hey. Dr. Tyler.

148
00:10:33.866 --> 00:10:35.697
I flew up to Anchorage this morning...

149
00:10:35.768 --> 00:10:39.226
...so I'm having
a bit of a slow start.

150
00:10:39.805 --> 00:10:42.865
Please. sit down and
make yourself comfortable.

151
00:10:53.285 --> 00:10:54.752
How are you?

152
00:10:54.820 --> 00:10:55.946
I'm all right.

153
00:10:56.856 --> 00:10:58.756
Have you been sleeping?

154
00:11:00.026 --> 00:11:01.755
It's...
It's worse.

155
00:11:03.796 --> 00:11:07.323
I wake up in the middle of
the night almost every night...

156
00:11:07.700 --> 00:11:09.497
...and I just lie there.

157
00:11:09.869 --> 00:11:12.429
What time does this normally occur?

158
00:11:12.505 --> 00:11:14.632
Around 2:30. 3:00
in the morning.

159
00:11:15.908 --> 00:11:18.706
And there's nothing
unusual waking you up?

160
00:11:19.011 --> 00:11:20.410
No. nothing.

161
00:11:21.047 --> 00:11:23.743
It's just there's...
There's one thing.

162
00:11:25.751 --> 00:11:29.016
There's an owl at my window.

163
00:11:32.491 --> 00:11:33.685
An owl?

164
00:11:38.831 --> 00:11:44.269
A white owl.
It was just looking at me.

165
00:11:48.040 --> 00:11:49.905
How long
was it there?

166
00:11:52.144 --> 00:11:54.112
Hours.

167
00:11:54.180 --> 00:11:57.513
No matter what I did.
it wouldn't fly away.

168
00:11:58.918 --> 00:12:00.818
It wasn't scared of me.

169
00:12:04.290 --> 00:12:05.951
What was it doing?

170
00:12:09.195 --> 00:12:10.924
Just staring at me.

171
00:12:18.671 --> 00:12:20.730
Had you ever seen it before?

172
00:12:22.441 --> 00:12:24.671
Yeah.

173
00:12:26.312 --> 00:12:28.280
Once when I was a kid.

174
00:12:28.347 --> 00:12:29.780
That was
the first time?

175
00:12:29.849 --> 00:12:30.975
Uh-huh.

176
00:12:33.052 --> 00:12:35.145
I guess I've
seen it a lot.

177
00:12:35.221 --> 00:12:36.711
How much is a lot?

178
00:12:36.789 --> 00:12:37.983
Every night this week.

179
00:12:38.057 --> 00:12:39.319
Every night?

180
00:12:40.192 --> 00:12:43.628
You mean every time you go to bed?

181
00:12:43.696 --> 00:12:45.186
I think it came inside.

182
00:12:46.732 --> 00:12:48.256
Was your window open?

183
00:12:48.334 --> 00:12:49.426
No.

184
00:12:51.203 --> 00:12:53.103
I wonder how
it got in.

185
00:12:53.405 --> 00:12:56.670
I don't know. but I remember
it looking down at me.

186
00:12:56.876 --> 00:12:58.309
Over your bed?

187
00:12:58.377 --> 00:13:01.210
Yeah. I think so.
I...

188
00:13:02.515 --> 00:13:04.710
It's really hard
to remember.

189
00:13:06.819 --> 00:13:10.585
It's almost like...
Like it didn't happen.

190
00:13:11.791 --> 00:13:14.521
Like. you know. in a dream.

191
00:13:17.296 --> 00:13:19.161
Like I just dreamt it.

192
00:13:20.766 --> 00:13:22.961
Can you come see me tomorrow?

193
00:13:23.869 --> 00:13:27.965
Sure. if you think I
should. or if it's important.

194
00:13:28.040 --> 00:13:31.498
Yeah. I do.
I do think it's important...

195
00:13:31.577 --> 00:13:35.138
...and it's nothing to
be alarmed at. at all...

196
00:13:37.082 --> 00:13:39.050
...but there have been some
strange coincidences here...

197
00:13:39.118 --> 00:13:42.986
...and I just... I feel like
I need to try something new.

198
00:13:43.622 --> 00:13:45.055
What do you mean?

199
00:13:45.124 --> 00:13:46.785
You're not the first patient I've had.

200
00:13:46.859 --> 00:13:49.726
who's experienced
something like this.

201
00:14:19.758 --> 00:14:22.886
I felt so sorry for my baby...

202
00:14:24.330 --> 00:14:27.629
...and I feel responsible.

203
00:14:28.200 --> 00:14:29.895
Can you just
knock it off?

204
00:14:29.969 --> 00:14:32.233
Conversion disorder
is not a phenomenon.

205
00:14:32.304 --> 00:14:34.363
...that a lot of
people understand...

206
00:14:34.907 --> 00:14:37.740
...and we've had to make
quite an adjustment.

207
00:14:39.945 --> 00:14:41.936
When did Ashley go blind?

208
00:14:42.615 --> 00:14:45.516
After what happened to Will...

209
00:14:45.584 --> 00:14:47.211
...she just lost her sight.

210
00:14:55.561 --> 00:14:57.358
Hey. baby.

211
00:14:57.429 --> 00:14:58.691
Hi. Mommy.

212
00:14:59.632 --> 00:15:01.930
How was rehearsal
for the play?

213
00:15:04.570 --> 00:15:06.595
Hey. what's wrong?

214
00:15:06.672 --> 00:15:08.071
Nothing.

215
00:15:16.248 --> 00:15:17.476
Come on.

216
00:15:24.256 --> 00:15:26.781
Come on. cough it up.
What happened?

217
00:15:28.460 --> 00:15:30.428
Ralph called me
a faker.

218
00:15:30.496 --> 00:15:32.987
What? A faker?

219
00:15:33.432 --> 00:15:34.865
He said that I could see before...

220
00:15:34.934 --> 00:15:36.731
...and now I was
just pretending.

221
00:15:36.802 --> 00:15:37.826
What a jerk.

222
00:15:37.903 --> 00:15:39.370
He said that I just wanted everybody.

223
00:15:39.438 --> 00:15:42.464
...to feel sorry for me because of Daddy.

224
00:16:05.264 --> 00:16:08.028
Dear Lord. thank you
for everything we have.

225
00:16:08.100 --> 00:16:10.125
Please continue
to bless our family...

226
00:16:10.703 --> 00:16:14.400
...and please continue to help
Ashley overcome her challenges...

227
00:16:15.441 --> 00:16:17.500
...and help
all of us to heal.

228
00:16:17.576 --> 00:16:20.010
In Jesus' name
we pray. Amen.

229
00:16:20.079 --> 00:16:21.239
Amen.

230
00:16:26.251 --> 00:16:27.684
Hey. what time is the game tomorrow?

231
00:16:27.753 --> 00:16:29.152
7:00.

232
00:16:29.788 --> 00:16:32.222
And who are you
playing again?

233
00:16:32.291 --> 00:16:33.986
I already told you.
Browerville.

234
00:16:35.728 --> 00:16:38.720
Well. I'm sorry. sweetie.
I must have forgot.

235
00:16:40.632 --> 00:16:42.259
Dad never forgot.

236
00:16:46.972 --> 00:16:50.203
Yeah. and Dad's
not here anymore.

237
00:16:53.679 --> 00:16:55.704
No. he's not.

238
00:17:00.119 --> 00:17:01.950
Can you
accept it yet?

239
00:17:02.021 --> 00:17:05.320
Okay. Ronnie. not in
front of your sister. okay?

240
00:17:05.391 --> 00:17:07.154
We'll talk
about it later.

241
00:17:07.226 --> 00:17:08.284
What do you mean?

242
00:17:08.360 --> 00:17:09.657
Nothing. honey.

243
00:17:12.097 --> 00:17:13.155
How Dad died.

244
00:17:13.232 --> 00:17:14.995
All right. Ronnie.
What is wrong with you?

245
00:17:15.067 --> 00:17:17.001
You go around helping other
people with their problems...

246
00:17:17.069 --> 00:17:18.536
Stop it.
Stop it!

247
00:17:18.604 --> 00:17:20.037
...but you can't even help yourself.

248
00:17:20.105 --> 00:17:22.801
What the hell is that supposed to mean?

249
00:17:23.976 --> 00:17:25.170
Ronnie.

250
00:17:27.479 --> 00:17:30.539
Mommy?
What did...

251
00:17:31.950 --> 00:17:33.645
What does he mean?

252
00:17:58.243 --> 00:18:00.677
And do you think he.
in any way...

253
00:18:00.746 --> 00:18:03.510
...may have blamed you for Will's death?

254
00:18:03.582 --> 00:18:05.379
Yes. he did blame me...

255
00:18:06.085 --> 00:18:11.284
...and he said that
I couldn't help him.

256
00:18:12.558 --> 00:18:15.652
...or Ashley or anyone.
and he was right.

257
00:18:54.066 --> 00:18:56.296
A small number continue to experience.

258
00:18:56.368 --> 00:18:59.496
...debilitating
sleep disorders...

259
00:18:59.571 --> 00:19:02.665
...and this seems to be the
trend throughout Nome...

260
00:19:02.741 --> 00:19:05.767
...and a cause
remains unknown.

261
00:19:07.379 --> 00:19:10.439
Even during the night
months. they can't sleep.

262
00:19:10.516 --> 00:19:13.713
We've seen over 300
people throughout Nome.

263
00:19:14.153 --> 00:19:16.883
who are all exhibiting
the same symptoms.

264
00:19:16.955 --> 00:19:20.118
Around 3:00 in the morning. they
are awakened for no apparent reason...

265
00:19:20.192 --> 00:19:24.959
...and they wake up apprehensive.
frightened. panicked...

266
00:19:26.198 --> 00:19:28.632
...as if something's
about to happen.

267
00:19:29.234 --> 00:19:30.223
Whether or not
this is related...

268
00:19:30.302 --> 00:19:31.291
Daddy?

269
00:19:31.370 --> 00:19:33.361
...to the missing people
or disappearances...

270
00:19:33.438 --> 00:19:35.303
No. my baby...

271
00:19:35.374 --> 00:19:37.399
...it's just a recording
of Daddy's voice.

272
00:19:39.478 --> 00:19:44.575
Come over here. I got
you. Come up on the bed.

273
00:19:48.654 --> 00:19:49.916
My angel.

274
00:20:02.000 --> 00:20:04.560
Okay. you're doing
real good. Tommy.

275
00:20:06.138 --> 00:20:10.074
When I get to one.
you will be asleep...

276
00:20:11.610 --> 00:20:13.942
...very. very relaxed.

277
00:20:15.514 --> 00:20:18.278
Four. three...

278
00:20:19.851 --> 00:20:23.947
...two and one.

279
00:20:34.600 --> 00:20:36.192
Can you hear me?

280
00:20:37.869 --> 00:20:38.961
Yes.

281
00:20:43.308 --> 00:20:44.297
And when was
the last time.

282
00:20:44.376 --> 00:20:46.606
...you had
trouble sleeping?

283
00:20:48.380 --> 00:20:49.745
Last night.

284
00:20:52.618 --> 00:20:54.586
And did you see the owl?

285
00:20:56.855 --> 00:20:57.947
Yeah.

286
00:21:02.361 --> 00:21:04.886
Good. And what did it look like?

287
00:21:04.963 --> 00:21:06.328
...what did it look like?

288
00:21:10.936 --> 00:21:12.096
Tommy?

289
00:21:13.672 --> 00:21:14.661
I...

290
00:21:16.642 --> 00:21:18.303
I don't remember.

291
00:21:18.844 --> 00:21:21.677
You don't remember
what the owl looks like?

292
00:21:22.481 --> 00:21:23.539
No.

293
00:21:24.449 --> 00:21:25.916
No. I don't see
the owl.

294
00:21:25.984 --> 00:21:27.918
I don't see
the owl now.

295
00:21:28.320 --> 00:21:29.309
It's not there
anymore.

296
00:21:29.388 --> 00:21:30.514
It's not
there anymore.

297
00:21:30.589 --> 00:21:31.578
Did it fly away?

298
00:21:31.657 --> 00:21:32.919
Did it fly away?

299
00:21:32.991 --> 00:21:34.288
No. I think it's...

300
00:21:34.359 --> 00:21:36.520
No.
I think it's...

301
00:21:37.863 --> 00:21:40.354
I don't really
remember it...

302
00:21:40.432 --> 00:21:43.526
I don't really
remember it...

303
00:21:45.904 --> 00:21:47.804
...ever
being there.

304
00:21:47.873 --> 00:21:49.397
...ever
being there.

305
00:21:58.517 --> 00:22:02.317
There's something outside
my door. It's gonna open it.

306
00:22:04.122 --> 00:22:06.682
The door's opening.

307
00:22:11.063 --> 00:22:12.257
Oh. my God.

308
00:22:12.464 --> 00:22:13.829
Oh. my God!

309
00:22:16.001 --> 00:22:17.798
No.

310
00:22:17.869 --> 00:22:19.200
What's wrong?

311
00:22:19.471 --> 00:22:21.268
- Oh. Jesus!
- Tommy. what's wrong?

312
00:22:21.340 --> 00:22:22.705
No. no. no!

313
00:22:22.941 --> 00:22:24.306
No. no!

314
00:22:24.676 --> 00:22:26.507
- No. no. no! No. no. no!
- Okay. Tommy. when I count to three...

315
00:22:26.578 --> 00:22:27.567
...you will awaken.

316
00:22:27.646 --> 00:22:28.840
No. no. no!

317
00:22:28.914 --> 00:22:30.074
- ... To conscious...
- No!

318
00:22:30.148 --> 00:22:31.410
- Three!
- No!

319
00:22:31.483 --> 00:22:33.348
No. no! No!

320
00:22:33.418 --> 00:22:34.942
- Three!
- No!

321
00:22:36.955 --> 00:22:38.855
Tommy.
it's not happening.

322
00:22:38.924 --> 00:22:40.824
It's a memory.
This is not real.

323
00:22:41.026 --> 00:22:42.391
It is real.

324
00:22:48.767 --> 00:22:50.257
Did I do that?

325
00:22:52.571 --> 00:22:55.972
Yeah. you did. Tommy.
but it's okay. It's okay.

326
00:23:00.245 --> 00:23:01.872
What did you see?

327
00:23:02.748 --> 00:23:03.737
Nothing.

328
00:23:03.815 --> 00:23:04.873
What?

329
00:23:05.450 --> 00:23:07.509
Nothing.

330
00:23:07.586 --> 00:23:09.110
You said
you saw something.

331
00:23:11.390 --> 00:23:14.553
No. I didn't
see anything.

332
00:23:16.261 --> 00:23:17.319
I didn't
see anything.

333
00:23:17.396 --> 00:23:19.091
I'm just trying
to help you.

334
00:23:19.164 --> 00:23:23.863
If you want to help me.
get me out of this room.

335
00:23:27.339 --> 00:23:32.174
I need to go home. I need to
go home. I'm okay. I'm okay.

336
00:23:32.477 --> 00:23:35.378
Tommy. are you trying
to convince me or you?

337
00:23:36.381 --> 00:23:39.282
Did you see what was
bothering you at night?

338
00:23:41.086 --> 00:23:42.849
Did you see the owl?

339
00:23:52.431 --> 00:23:55.958
Can we talk about this next time?

340
00:23:57.669 --> 00:23:59.864
Yeah. of course.
Sure.

341
00:24:02.541 --> 00:24:04.668
Talk to me
when you need to.

342
00:24:05.310 --> 00:24:08.643
Yeah. Okay.

343
00:24:50.322 --> 00:24:53.416
Call in EMTs. Search.
everybody. I want everybody.

344
00:24:53.492 --> 00:24:57.394
Transfer me into that house. Right now.

345
00:25:07.906 --> 00:25:08.895
Tommy here.

346
00:25:08.974 --> 00:25:10.805
Yeah. what's going on in there?

347
00:25:11.009 --> 00:25:12.408
I want to talk
to Abbey Tyler.

348
00:25:12.477 --> 00:25:13.705
Abbey?

349
00:25:13.778 --> 00:25:16.144
Abbey's not here right now.
but I can help you.

350
00:25:16.214 --> 00:25:17.738
I have to
talk to her!

351
00:25:22.854 --> 00:25:23.912
Hello?

352
00:25:23.989 --> 00:25:25.854
I need you down
here at Tommy's house.

353
00:25:26.391 --> 00:25:27.653
- August?
- He's gone crazy.

354
00:25:27.726 --> 00:25:30.092
He's holding his family
hostage. and he's asking for you.

355
00:25:30.195 --> 00:25:31.856
Okay. I'll be
right there.

356
00:25:45.377 --> 00:25:46.366
Bring her up here.

357
00:25:46.444 --> 00:25:47.468
She's here right now.

358
00:25:47.546 --> 00:25:49.741
We'll walk her up to you. okay.
Tommy? It's gonna be all right.

359
00:25:49.814 --> 00:25:52.009
Just give her the phone. Give her
the phone. I want to talk to her.

360
00:25:52.083 --> 00:25:54.051
- Both arms out. Both arms out.
- She's here.

361
00:25:54.119 --> 00:25:55.518
Put her on the phone right now.

362
00:25:55.587 --> 00:25:57.555
- I'm gonna do it right now. okay?
- Is this really necessary?

363
00:25:57.622 --> 00:25:59.522
- I want to talk to her!
- Can somebody tell me what's going on?

364
00:25:59.591 --> 00:26:00.615
- Where is she?
- Take it easy. all right?

365
00:26:00.692 --> 00:26:03.183
- I don't see her. Get her up here!
- August. what's going on?

366
00:26:03.261 --> 00:26:06.355
I need you to calm him down
and get him thinking rationally.

367
00:26:06.431 --> 00:26:08.626
He's got Sarah. Timothy and Joe lined up.

368
00:26:08.700 --> 00:26:10.998
...in the kitchen with
a gun to their heads...

369
00:26:11.069 --> 00:26:13.367
...and he wants to talk to you
for some reason. all right?

370
00:26:13.438 --> 00:26:14.462
Watch your step.

371
00:26:14.539 --> 00:26:15.904
Straight this way.

372
00:26:15.974 --> 00:26:20.377
Tommy? Tommy. what...
What's going on here?

373
00:26:21.346 --> 00:26:23.940
I'm so sorry.
but I've gotta do this.

374
00:26:25.917 --> 00:26:27.214
I don't have
a choice.

375
00:26:27.285 --> 00:26:32.689
It was completely surreal to be
there in the middle of the night.

376
00:26:33.358 --> 00:26:35.553
with all those
police trucks.

377
00:26:35.727 --> 00:26:36.853
I don't have
a choice.

378
00:26:36.928 --> 00:26:38.327
No. no. no. You have a choice. Tommy.

379
00:26:38.396 --> 00:26:39.761
We always
have a choice.

380
00:26:39.831 --> 00:26:41.526
- Not this time.
- Please. Tommy!

381
00:26:41.600 --> 00:26:43.568
Yes. Yes. you do.
You have the choice.

382
00:26:43.635 --> 00:26:46.103
...right now to just... To just stop.

383
00:26:46.204 --> 00:26:48.934
Just put down
the gun. Tommy.

384
00:26:49.007 --> 00:26:51.840
You have it within
your power to just stop.

385
00:26:51.910 --> 00:26:54.003
Please. before
somebody gets hurt.

386
00:26:54.079 --> 00:26:56.172
Tommy. look at
Sarah. Tommy.

387
00:26:56.247 --> 00:26:57.714
Look at...
Look at your wife.

388
00:26:58.450 --> 00:26:59.576
Look at your
children. Tommy.

389
00:26:59.651 --> 00:27:00.675
It's okay.
It's okay.

390
00:27:00.752 --> 00:27:03.016
You would never let
anything happen to them.

391
00:27:03.088 --> 00:27:04.487
You love them
so much.

392
00:27:04.556 --> 00:27:06.786
I know what keeps us up at night.

393
00:27:06.858 --> 00:27:10.316
And if you saw
what I saw...

394
00:27:10.395 --> 00:27:11.521
...you would
understand.

395
00:27:11.596 --> 00:27:13.564
What did you
see. Tommy?

396
00:27:13.965 --> 00:27:15.432
It doesn't matter.
because we're not gonna.

397
00:27:15.500 --> 00:27:18.196
...have to see it
ever again.

398
00:27:18.436 --> 00:27:21.428
Just wait. Tommy.
I can help you.

399
00:27:21.573 --> 00:27:24.667
Just talk to me. okay? We'll
talk as long as you need to.

400
00:27:24.743 --> 00:27:26.005
We'll get
through this. Tommy.

401
00:27:26.077 --> 00:27:27.806
If anybody's got a
clear shot. take it now.

402
00:27:27.879 --> 00:27:28.937
Negative.

403
00:27:29.014 --> 00:27:31.039
I don't have a clear shot. sir.
The wife is blocking him.

404
00:27:31.116 --> 00:27:32.174
And he wasn't
listening to me.

405
00:27:32.250 --> 00:27:33.410
Do you know what
Zimabu Eter means?

406
00:27:33.485 --> 00:27:34.577
And they were
going to kill him.

407
00:27:34.653 --> 00:27:37.486
What? Wait. I can't
hear you. Tommy. What?

408
00:27:37.555 --> 00:27:38.852
Has anybody
got the shot?

409
00:27:38.923 --> 00:27:42.415
Zimabu Eter! Zimabu Eter! Zimabu Eter!

410
00:27:42.494 --> 00:27:43.620
What the hell
does that mean?

411
00:27:43.928 --> 00:27:45.953
- Zimabu Eter? I don't know. Tommy.
- What the hell does that mean?

412
00:27:46.031 --> 00:27:47.055
Anybody got
the goddamn shot?

413
00:27:47.132 --> 00:27:49.066
But I can find out. Just
give me a little time.

414
00:27:49.134 --> 00:27:50.294
I need to know now!

415
00:27:50.368 --> 00:27:51.494
Just give me
a little time.

416
00:27:51.569 --> 00:27:53.434
- I will find out for you. I promise.
- Right now!

417
00:27:53.505 --> 00:27:54.631
No. please!

418
00:27:54.706 --> 00:27:55.798
You can't help me.

419
00:27:56.975 --> 00:27:58.340
I love you.

420
00:27:59.844 --> 00:28:01.471
Move. move!

421
00:28:03.548 --> 00:28:05.516
Move. move. move!

422
00:28:05.650 --> 00:28:07.618
Tommy! God damn it!

423
00:28:36.648 --> 00:28:39.276
I'm having a hard time.

424
00:28:39.350 --> 00:28:40.647
...understanding what
happened here.

425
00:28:42.220 --> 00:28:43.949
I know. I know.

426
00:28:44.622 --> 00:28:47.090
- You don't know what he saw?
- So you have no idea what he saw?

427
00:28:47.158 --> 00:28:48.489
- He didn't tell me.
- He didn't tell me.

428
00:28:48.560 --> 00:28:50.357
What did
he tell you?

429
00:28:53.565 --> 00:28:57.501
That what he thought
he saw wasn't an owl.

430
00:28:57.569 --> 00:28:58.831
That it was
something else.

431
00:28:59.604 --> 00:29:02.505
And that's what was
keeping him up at night?

432
00:29:03.141 --> 00:29:04.233
Yeah.

433
00:29:06.478 --> 00:29:09.606
So he was under hypnosis
when he saw this?

434
00:29:12.951 --> 00:29:14.043
Yeah.

435
00:29:14.452 --> 00:29:17.182
And how do you know
what he saw was real?

436
00:29:17.856 --> 00:29:19.847
I don't know
that it was.

437
00:29:20.024 --> 00:29:22.219
So what you're saying is that
Tommy might have done all of this.

438
00:29:22.293 --> 00:29:24.523
...based on something
that was imaginary.

439
00:29:31.569 --> 00:29:35.027
All I know is that he
believed what he saw...

440
00:29:36.374 --> 00:29:37.966
...and there was more fear in his eyes.

441
00:29:38.042 --> 00:29:40.237
...than I've ever
seen in my life.

442
00:29:40.345 --> 00:29:43.473
Had you not
hypnotized him...

443
00:29:43.548 --> 00:29:45.379
...do you think he would have done this?

444
00:29:48.520 --> 00:29:50.147
What do you mean?

445
00:29:51.256 --> 00:29:53.053
I'm just
wondering...

446
00:29:53.124 --> 00:29:54.318
without this
hypnotism...

447
00:29:55.527 --> 00:29:58.894
...do you think he still would
have murdered his family?

448
00:30:03.835 --> 00:30:07.327
That is a ridiculous
and offensive question.

449
00:30:07.472 --> 00:30:09.633
No. what's ridiculous and offensive.

450
00:30:09.707 --> 00:30:11.675
...is that an entire family
is lying in a morgue.

451
00:30:11.743 --> 00:30:13.506
...from a murder-suicide...

452
00:30:13.578 --> 00:30:14.670
...and the last
meaningful contact.

453
00:30:14.746 --> 00:30:16.873
...that the murderer
had was with you.

454
00:30:16.948 --> 00:30:18.415
No. what
happened tonight.

455
00:30:18.483 --> 00:30:21.008
would have manifested itself eventually.

456
00:30:21.820 --> 00:30:24.015
He was suppressing
something.

457
00:30:24.589 --> 00:30:26.113
Look. in 13 years
of practice...

458
00:30:26.191 --> 00:30:29.558
I've never witnessed
something to this extent.

459
00:30:29.894 --> 00:30:32.226
Abbey. why didn't
you contact us.

460
00:30:33.031 --> 00:30:34.931
...if you suspected
he was unstable.

461
00:30:35.066 --> 00:30:37.000
...after an admittedly
violent episode?

462
00:30:37.068 --> 00:30:40.060
He was completely coherent
when he left my office.

463
00:30:40.138 --> 00:30:42.572
Now. I had no reason to suspect...

464
00:30:42.774 --> 00:30:44.435
I called his wife to ask
her to keep an eye on him.

465
00:30:44.509 --> 00:30:46.238
And now
she's dead.

466
00:30:52.250 --> 00:30:54.980
Okay. I'm not going
to sit here and listen.

467
00:30:55.053 --> 00:30:57.647
...to how hypnosis-induced
murder caused this.

468
00:30:57.722 --> 00:30:59.622
- Jesus. I am trying to find out...
- This is ridiculous.

469
00:30:59.691 --> 00:31:03.422
...what caused one of the worst
murders in the history of Nome.

470
00:31:03.494 --> 00:31:06.224
There's something going on in
this town that we don't understand.

471
00:31:06.297 --> 00:31:08.731
There's something happening
to people in their sleep...

472
00:31:08.800 --> 00:31:10.324
Well. I don't know
about any of that!

473
00:31:10.401 --> 00:31:12.232
I don't understand what
you're talking about!

474
00:31:12.303 --> 00:31:13.736
I don't deal
in hallucinations.

475
00:31:13.805 --> 00:31:15.602
I don't deal in the
visions in the ether.

476
00:31:15.673 --> 00:31:16.970
What in the hell are you talking about?

477
00:31:17.041 --> 00:31:18.736
I'm dealing in real
flesh and blood things...

478
00:31:18.810 --> 00:31:21.278
...four of whom are lying
on slabs next door.

479
00:31:21.346 --> 00:31:23.439
How dare you? My husband was
lying on one of those slabs.

480
00:31:23.514 --> 00:31:24.674
...and you still
haven't found his killer.

481
00:31:24.749 --> 00:31:26.580
Abbey. now. you know damn
well what happened to Will.

482
00:31:26.651 --> 00:31:27.675
That case is closed.

483
00:31:27.752 --> 00:31:29.219
No. you cannot
file things away.

484
00:31:29.287 --> 00:31:30.686
without getting to
what really happened.

485
00:31:30.755 --> 00:31:34.054
Now. there are more unsolved
murders and missing people in Nome...

486
00:31:34.125 --> 00:31:35.888
- Sit down.
- ... Than any other town in Alaska...

487
00:31:35.960 --> 00:31:38.428
...three years of which have
been under your watch.

488
00:31:38.496 --> 00:31:40.726
Now. what is happening
in this town is very real...

489
00:31:40.798 --> 00:31:41.822
...and it must be
acknowledged.

490
00:31:41.900 --> 00:31:43.492
Sit down!

491
00:31:53.578 --> 00:31:56.206
You stop whatever this
governmental study is...

492
00:31:56.281 --> 00:31:58.181
...this hypnosis.
whatever it is...

493
00:31:58.249 --> 00:32:00.080
whatever you and
Will were after.

494
00:32:00.151 --> 00:32:02.779
It's bringing nothing but bad
news to a town that's had enough.

495
00:32:02.854 --> 00:32:04.219
Now. I don't care how
important it is to you.

496
00:32:04.289 --> 00:32:07.588
I don't care how hard you've
worked on it. I don't care.

497
00:32:07.659 --> 00:32:11.117
You're not gonna use the people
of Nome for a goddamn rat study.

498
00:32:24.142 --> 00:32:27.043
I felt responsible for...

499
00:32:28.846 --> 00:32:31.076
...death.
and his family's.

500
00:32:33.017 --> 00:32:35.713
And at the time. after
all that happened...

501
00:32:35.787 --> 00:32:38.688
I still didn't know why he did it.

502
00:32:41.993 --> 00:32:45.156
All of the patients
reported seeing the same owl...

503
00:32:47.065 --> 00:32:52.935
...but Tommy mentioned that his
memory of the owl was wrong.

504
00:32:54.706 --> 00:32:58.073
...and that he didn't
see it anymore.

505
00:32:58.142 --> 00:33:01.441
It was some sort of
false recollection.

506
00:33:05.984 --> 00:33:07.576
The question is...

507
00:33:09.554 --> 00:33:12.921
...if under hypnosis. will the
others feel the same way?

508
00:33:16.794 --> 00:33:18.819
Will they see
what he saw?

509
00:33:24.102 --> 00:33:26.832
